<div id="review_1007409133" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1007409133" />
    <a title="Sivananthi T" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8409829-sivananthi-t"><img alt="Sivananthi T" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1345065660p2/8409829.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1007409133?book_show_action=true">Jul 26, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sivananthi T" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sivananthi T" href="/user/show/8409829-sivananthi-t">Sivananthi T</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780141190020" href="/book/show/11914145-incident-at-vichy">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1007409133" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15822926460347240860">Miller examines the passivity which enabled the Holocaust to take place. The paralysis and inability of people to determine their personal moral compass amidst turbulent times, and determine a series of actions from that points to a recurrent theme in society again and again. When faced with the unspeakable, the reactions of trying to comprehend, engage and then draw a line of resistance is not easy. To keep the eye on the end game despite chaos, is the only way we will survive with our morality</span>
  <span id="freeText15822926460347240860" style="display:none">Miller examines the passivity which enabled the Holocaust to take place. The paralysis and inability of people to determine their personal moral compass amidst turbulent times, and determine a series of actions from that points to a recurrent theme in society again and again. When faced with the unspeakable, the reactions of trying to comprehend, engage and then draw a line of resistance is not easy. To keep the eye on the end game despite chaos, is the only way we will survive with our morality intact.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15822926460347240860" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


