<div id="review_2745672873" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2745672873" />
    <a title="Marge" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2638219-marge"><img alt="Marge" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2745672873?book_show_action=true">Mar 10, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marge" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marge" href="/user/show/2638219-marge">Marge</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2745672873" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14780486777704057036">In 1942 Vichy, France, a group of men have been called in for questioning by the Nazis and French police. They have been given no reason but think it might be because they are suspected of being Jewish. Awaiting to be called into the Major&apos;s office for individual questioning, they talk about what they should do -- fight back, escape? <br/>There&apos;s a line that says &quot;Each man has his Jew; it is the other.&quot; I think that&apos;s what playwright Arthur Miller is really trying to say in this play written in the e</span>
  <span id="freeText14780486777704057036" style="display:none">In 1942 Vichy, France, a group of men have been called in for questioning by the Nazis and French police. They have been given no reason but think it might be because they are suspected of being Jewish. Awaiting to be called into the Major's office for individual questioning, they talk about what they should do -- fight back, escape? <br />There's a line that says "Each man has his Jew; it is the other." I think that's what playwright Arthur Miller is really trying to say in this play written in the early 1960s. Although this is set in early World War II, that's what makes it relevant in any age. We may or may not discriminate against someone who is Jewish but we have some class of people that we persecute.<br />I think this play would be better seen than read. It's not a long one but it's hard to keep everything straight on the page.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14780486777704057036" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


